# Multi-Robot ROS 2 SLAM & Navigation – Husky A200
**Principal Engineer:** Abiola Arowolo (Senior Systems Engineer)
**Supervisor:** Prof. Doyun Lee | **Institution:** GSOU
**Project Status:** [INFO] Task 2B - SLAM & Autonomous Navigation
**Current Audit Timestamp:** 2026-03-10 14:10:22
**Environment:** ROS 2 Humble | Gazebo 11 | Ubuntu 22.04 (WSL2)

---

## 🛠 Project Overview
Implementation of high-reliability SLAM and autonomous navigation for the **Clearpath Husky A200** within a warehouse environment. This repository executes Task 2B, prioritizing minimalist logic and robust audit trails for multi-robot scalability.



---

## 📁 Workspace Architecture & State
Managed via `~/ros2_ws` (Symlinked to `/mnt/x/ros2_ws`). **Structural paths are immutable.**

```text
~/ros2_ws/
├── src/
│   ├── my_robot_pkg/           # Task 1 Deliverables (Read-Only)
│   ├── multi_robot_bringup/    # Operational Launch Logic
│   │   └── launch/
│   │       └── husky_slam_warehouse.launch.py
│   └── nav_config/             # System Parameters
│       └── husky_slam_params.yaml
├── maps/                       # High-Precision Occupancy Grids
│   ├── husky_map.pgm
│   └── husky_map.yaml
├── logs/                       # [NON-NEGOTIABLE] Mandatory Audit Trail
│   └── session_history.log     # Forensic record of all deployments
├── husky_nav2_params.yaml      # Navigation2 Tuning
└── husky_workshop.world        # Custom Gazebo World (Optional)# Multi-Robot ROS2 Workspace
